Subject: Re: [T2] loss of oil pressure symptoms

On Sat, Feb 08, 2003 at 10:22:00AM -0800, paul gould wrote:
> My newly rebuilt 2 liter suffered the oil pressure light coming on
> yesterday.  During my break in period, I have been using straight 30
> wt oil. I have got about 400 miles on the new engine.   The light
> came on at idle, about 800 rpms, would go out at 1100 rpms.  This is
> after driving for 60 miles with one stop to check on things. I drove
> up to a ski resort, nice easy gradual accent. the temp was about 22,
> elevation 4500 when I stopped and the light came on.  Should I be
> concerned?  Is it just because the cold temp and oil wt.?  

Obviously low oil pressure is a bad thing. But there have been many
people who have mentioned and experienced the oil pressure switch
being tripped at a lower pressure than the stock one. Is your pressure
switch a new one or an old one?

